# BokaNära - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
BokaNära is a Swedish platform for local businesses. Customers can search, discover, and book services with SMS reminders.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Firebase (Auth, Firestore, Storage, Functions)
- Vercel (Hosting)

## Directory Structure
- `/app` - Next.js pages and routes
- `/components` - Reusable React components
- `/services` - Business logic and API calls
- `/context` - React Context providers
- `/lib` - Utilities and configurations
- `/functions` - Firebase Cloud Functions

## Coding Standards
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Follow Swedish naming conventions for user-facing text
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Prefer server components when possible
- Use 'use client' only when necessary

## Firebase Collections
- `users` - User profiles
- `companies` - Business listings
- `bookings` - Appointment bookings
- `reviews` - Customer reviews
- `notifications` - In-app notifications
- `reminders` - SMS reminder queue

## Environment Variables
All Firebase config uses `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_*` prefix.
